rows.text: Delta control failure at T+108 seconds. RSO destruct.
Launch failure. Centaur electrical disconnect malfunction. No orbit.

Launch failure. Gas generator leak caused a fire in the Atlas's engine compartment leading to loss of control starting at T+30 seconds. Payload fairing and satellite were stripped away, followed by RSO destruct of the Atlas at T+43 seconds. The Centaur was ejected from the exploding booster intact and the destruct command was sent to it a few seconds later.
Launch failure. Centaur broke up in orbit, making it impossible for the satellite to attain its intended altitude.
Launch failure, carrier rocket went out of control two seconds after launch
Launched, second solar panel failed to deploy
Reduced power due to solar reflector fogging
Out of control, later fully active
